WEBVTT

00:22.540 --> 00:23.940
XXIX.

00:24.860 --> 00:30.220
The recollection of about three days and nights succeeding this is very dim in my mind.

00:30.740 --> 00:36.600
I can recall some sensations felt in that interval, but few thoughts framed and no actions

00:36.600 --> 00:43.240
performed. I knew I was in a small room and in a narrow bed. To that bed I seemed to have grown.

00:43.900 --> 00:49.780
I lay on it motionless as a stone, and to have torn me from it would have been almost to kill me.

00:49.780 --> 00:57.520
I took no note of the lapse of time, of the change from morning to noon, from noon to evening.

00:58.060 --> 01:03.220
I observed when anyone entered or left the apartment. I could even tell who they were.

01:03.700 --> 01:09.460
I could understand what was said when the speaker stood near to me, but I could not answer. To open

01:09.460 --> 01:16.540
my lips or move my limbs was equally impossible. Hannah, the servant, was my most frequent visitor.

01:16.540 --> 01:22.740
Her coming disturbed me. I had a feeling that she wished me away, that she did not understand

01:22.740 --> 01:30.060
me or my circumstances, that she was prejudiced against me. Diana and Mary appeared in the chamber

01:30.060 --> 01:35.160
once or twice a day. They would whisper sentences of this sort at my bedside.

01:36.020 --> 01:46.500
It is very well we took her in. Yes, she would certainly have been found dead at the door in

01:46.500 --> 01:51.780
strange hardships, I imagine. Poor, emaciated, pallid wanderer.

01:52.940 --> 01:59.460
She is not an uneducated person, I should think, by her manner of speaking. Her accent was quite

01:59.460 --> 02:04.940
pure, and the clothes she took off, though splashed and wet, were little worn and fine.

02:06.060 --> 02:13.680
She has a peculiar face, fleshlish and haggard as it is, I rather like it. And when in good health

02:13.680 --> 02:20.460
and animated I can fancy her physiognomy would be agreeable. Never once in their dialogues did I

02:20.460 --> 02:26.560
hear a syllable of regret at the hospitality they had extended to me, or of suspicion of,

02:26.660 --> 02:34.700
or aversion to, myself. I was comforted. Mr. St. John came but once. He looked at me and said

02:34.700 --> 02:43.660
my state of lethargy was the result of reaction from excessive and protracted fatigue. He

02:43.660 --> 02:49.140
nature he was sure would manage best left to herself. He said every nerve had been

02:49.140 --> 02:55.840
overstrained in some way, and the whole system must sleep torpid a while. There was no disease.

02:56.240 --> 03:02.000
He imagined my recovery would be rapid enough when once commenced. These opinions he delivered

03:02.000 --> 03:08.960
in a few words in a quiet low voice, and added after a pause in the tone of a man little accustomed

03:08.960 --> 03:18.240
to expansive comment, rather an unusual physiognomy, certainly not indicative of vulgarity

03:18.240 --> 03:25.860
or degradation. Far otherwise, responded Diana, to speak truth, St. John, my heart rather warms to

03:25.860 --> 03:32.140
the poor little soul. I wish we may be able to benefit her permanently. That is hardly likely,

03:32.160 --> 03:37.800
was the reply. You will find she is some young lady who has had a misunderstanding with her friends,

03:37.800 --> 03:43.960
and has probably injudiciously left them. We may perhaps succeed in restoring her to them

03:43.960 --> 03:49.420
if she is not obstinate, but I trace lines of force in her face which make me skeptical

03:49.420 --> 03:56.180
of her tractability. He stood considering me some minutes, then added. She looks sensible,

03:56.640 --> 04:04.200
but not at all handsome. She is so ill, St. John. Ill or well, she would always be plain.

04:04.200 --> 04:07.900
The grace and harmony of beauty are quite wanting in those features.

04:08.380 --> 04:15.180
On the third day I was better. On the fourth I could speak, move, rise, in bed, and turn.

04:16.320 --> 04:20.920
Hannah had brought me some gruel and dry toast, about, as I suppose, the dinner hour.

04:21.480 --> 04:27.620
I had eaten with relish. The food was good, void of the feverish flavor which had hitherto poisoned

04:27.620 --> 04:33.060
what I had swallowed. When she left me I felt comparatively strong and revived.

04:34.020 --> 04:40.660
Ere long satiety of repose and desire for action stirred me. I wished to rise, but what could I put

04:40.660 --> 04:47.060
on? Only my damp and bemired apparel, in which I had slept on the ground and fallen in the marsh.

04:47.640 --> 04:55.100
I felt ashamed to appear before my benefactor so clad. I was spared the humiliation. On the

04:55.100 --> 05:01.160
bedside were all my own things, clean and dry. My black silk frock hung against the wall.

05:01.600 --> 05:06.520
The traces of the bog were removed from it. The creases left by the wet smoothed out.

05:06.820 --> 05:12.400
It was quite decent. My very shoes and stockings were purified and rendered presentable.

05:13.060 --> 05:17.320
There were the means of washing in the room, and a comb and brush to smooth my hair.

05:18.000 --> 05:23.760
After a weary process, and resting every five minutes, I succeeded in dressing myself.

05:24.420 --> 05:30.520
My clothes hung loose on me, for I was much wasted, but I covered deficiencies with a shawl,

05:30.960 --> 05:36.700
and once more clean and respectable looking. No speck of the dirt, no trace of the disorder

05:36.700 --> 05:43.640
I so hated, and which seemed so to degrade me, left. I crept down a stone staircase with the

05:43.640 --> 05:49.380
aid of the banisters, to a narrow low passage, and found my way presently to the kitchen.

05:50.280 --> 05:55.120
It was full of the fragrance of new bread, and the warmth of a generous fire.

05:55.780 --> 06:02.160
Hannah was baking. Prejudices, it is well known, are most difficult to eradicate from the heart

06:02.160 --> 06:08.520
whose soil has never been loosened or fertilized by education. They grow there firm as weeds among

06:08.520 --> 06:15.520
stones. Hannah had been cold and stiff indeed at the first. Latterly she had begun to relent a

06:15.520 --> 06:19.600
and when she saw me come in tidy and well dressed, she even smiled.

06:20.360 --> 06:25.900
What, you have got up, she said. You are better then. You may sit you down in my chair,

06:25.960 --> 06:32.740
on the hearthstone, if you will. She pointed to the rocking chair. I took it. She bustled about,

06:32.940 --> 06:38.220
examining me every now and then from the corner of her eye. Turning to me as she took some loaves

06:38.220 --> 06:43.140
from the oven, she asked bluntly, Did you ever go a-begging afore you came here?

06:43.620 --> 06:49.140
I was indignant for a moment, but remembering that anger was out of the question, and that I

06:49.140 --> 06:54.840
had indeed appeared as a beggar to her, I answered quietly, but still not without a certain marked

06:54.840 --> 07:02.100
firmness. You are mistaken in supposing me a beggar. I am no beggar, any more than yourself

07:02.100 --> 07:09.400
or your young ladies. After a pause she said, I done it understand that. You've like no house,

07:09.400 --> 07:15.940
nor no brass, I guess. The want of house or brass, by which I suppose you mean money,

07:16.360 --> 07:21.980
does not make a beggar in your sense of the word. Are you book-learned? she inquired presently.

07:22.500 --> 07:29.100
Yes, very. But you've never been to a boarding school? I was at a boarding school eight years.

07:29.620 --> 07:36.900
She opened her eyes wide. Whatever cannot you keep yourself for then? I have kept myself,

07:36.900 --> 07:42.740
and I trust shall keep myself again. What are you going to do with these gooseberries? I inquired,

07:42.820 --> 07:49.360
as she brought out a basket of the fruit. Make them into pies. Give them to me, and I'll pick them.

07:49.820 --> 07:57.340
Nay, I don't want you to do not. But I must do something. Let me have them. She consented,

07:57.360 --> 08:03.500
and she even brought me a clean towel to spread over my dress, lest, she said, I should mucky it.

08:04.840 --> 08:10.760
You've not been used to a servant's work, I see by your hands, she remarked. Happen you've been a dressmaker?

08:11.720 --> 08:17.940
No, you are wrong. And now never mind what I have been. Don't trouble your head further about me.

08:18.300 --> 08:23.760
But tell me the name of the house where we are. Some calls it Marsh End, and some calls it Moore

08:23.760 --> 08:31.040
House. And the gentleman who lives here is called Mr. St. John? Nay, he doesn't live here. He is only

08:31.040 --> 08:37.480
staying awhile. When he is at home, he is in his own parish at Morton. That village a few miles off?

08:37.640 --> 08:45.620
Aye. And what is he? He is a parson. I remembered the answer of the old housekeeper at the parsonage

08:45.620 --> 08:52.700
when I had asked to see the clergyman. This, then, was his father's residence? Aye. Old Mr.

08:52.700 --> 08:59.340
John Rivers lived here, and his father and grandfather and great-grandfather afore him.

09:00.720 --> 09:07.100
The name, then, of that gentleman is Mr. St. John Rivers? Aye, St. John is like his cursand name.

09:08.100 --> 09:14.400
And his sisters are called Diana and Mary Rivers? Yes. Their father is dead?

09:15.320 --> 09:22.000
Dead three weeks' sin of a stroke. They have no mother? The mistress has been dead this money a

09:22.000 --> 09:28.680
year. Have you lived with the family long? I have lived here thirty years. I nursed them all

09:28.680 --> 09:35.340
three. That proves you must have been an honest and faithful servant. I will say so much for you,

09:35.420 --> 09:41.200
though you have had the incivility to call me a beggar. She again regarded me with a surprised

09:41.200 --> 09:47.940
stare. I believe, she said, I was quite mistaken in my thoughts of you. But there are so many

09:47.940 --> 09:52.860
cheats goes about. You must forgive me. And though I continued rather severely,

09:53.080 --> 09:57.380
you wished to turn me from the door on a night when you should not have shut out a dog.

09:58.280 --> 10:04.580
Well, it was hard. But what can a body do? I thought more of the children nor of myself.

10:04.820 --> 10:10.640
Poor things! They have liked nobody to take care of them but me. I like to look sharpish.

10:11.040 --> 10:13.780
I maintained a grave silence for some minutes.

10:14.560 --> 10:18.340
You might not think too hardly of me, she again remarked.

10:19.360 --> 10:24.760
But I do think hardly of you, I said, and I'll tell you why. Not so much because you refused to

10:24.760 --> 10:30.480
give me shelter or regarded me as an impostor, as because you just now made it a species of

10:30.480 --> 10:36.440
reproach that I had no brass and no house. Some of the best people that ever lived have been as

10:36.440 --> 10:41.400
destitute as I am, and if you are a Christian you ought not to consider poverty a crime.

10:42.320 --> 10:48.700
No more I ought, said she. Mr. St. John tells me so, too. And I see I wore wrong.

10:49.320 --> 10:55.600
But I've clear, different notion on you now to what I had. You look a right down decent little

10:55.600 --> 11:04.200
crater. That will do. I forgive you now. Shake hands. She put her flowery and horny hand into

11:04.200 --> 11:10.040
mine. Another and heartier smile illumined her rough face, and from that moment we were friends.

11:11.460 --> 11:16.840
Hannah was evidently fond of talking. While I picked the fruit and she made the paste for the

11:16.840 --> 11:21.660
pies, she proceeded to give me sundry details about her deceased master and mistress,

11:22.080 --> 11:28.480
and the children, as she called the young people. Old Mr. Rivers, she said, was a plain man enough,

11:28.560 --> 11:34.780
but a gentleman, and of as ancient a family as could be found. Marsh End had belonged to

11:34.780 --> 11:40.180
Rivers ever since it was a house, and it was, she affirmed, a bound two hundred year old,

11:40.220 --> 11:45.020
for all it looked but a small humble place, not to compare with Mr. Oliver's grand hall

11:45.020 --> 11:50.000
down in Morton Vale, but she could remember Bill Oliver's father a journeyman needle-maker,

11:50.460 --> 11:55.940
and the Rivers were gentry in the old days of the Henrys, as anybody might see by looking

11:55.940 --> 12:03.260
into the registers, in Morton Church vestry. Still, she allowed, the old master was like other folk,

12:03.260 --> 12:09.860
not much out of the common way, stark mad a shooting and farming and suchlike. The mistress

12:09.860 --> 12:16.260
was different. She was a great reader, and studied a deal, and the barons had taken after her.

12:16.920 --> 12:22.040
There was nothing like them in these parts, nor ever had been. They had liked learning,

12:22.100 --> 12:27.580
all three almost from the time they could speak, and they had always been of a meck of their own.

12:28.320 --> 12:33.080
Mr. St. John, when he grew up, would go to college and be a parson, and the girls,

12:33.100 --> 12:38.440
as soon as they left school, would seek places as governesses, for they had told their father

12:38.440 --> 12:45.400
that some years ago lost a great deal of money by a man he had trusted turning bankrupt, and as he

12:45.400 --> 12:51.360
was now not rich enough to give them fortunes, they must provide for themselves. They had lived

12:51.360 --> 12:56.640
very little at home for a long while, and were only now come to stay a few weeks on account of

12:56.640 --> 13:02.660
their father's death. But they did so like Marsh End and Morton, and all these moors and hills about.

13:03.200 --> 13:07.640
They had been in London and many other grand towns, but they always said there was no place

13:07.640 --> 13:13.440
like home. And then they were so agreeable with each other, never fell out nor threeped.

13:13.740 --> 13:16.940
She did not know where there was such a family for being united.

13:17.980 --> 13:22.720
Having finished my task of gooseberry picking, I asked where the two ladies and their brother were

13:22.720 --> 13:28.920
now. Gone over to Morton for a walk, but they would be back in half an hour to tea.

13:30.120 --> 13:36.560
They returned within the time Hannah had allotted them. They entered by the kitchen door. Mr. St.

13:36.600 --> 13:42.660
John, when he saw me, merely bowed and passed through. The two ladies stopped. Mary, in a few

13:42.660 --> 13:48.080
words, kindly and calmly expressing the pleasure she felt in seeing me well enough to be able to

13:48.080 --> 13:52.440
come down. Diana took my hand. She shook her head at me.

13:52.920 --> 13:58.740
You should have waited for my leave to descend, she said. You still look very pale, and so thin.

13:59.000 --> 14:01.060
Poor child! Poor girl!

14:02.260 --> 14:08.480
Diana had a voice toned to my ear like the cooing of a dove. She possessed eyes whose gaze I

14:08.480 --> 14:14.380
delighted to encounter. Her whole face seemed to me full of charm. Mary's countenance was

14:14.380 --> 14:19.960
equally intelligent, her features equally pretty, but her expression was more reserved,

14:20.320 --> 14:25.800
and her manners, though gentle, more distant. Diana looked and spoke with a certain authority.

14:26.300 --> 14:31.560
She had a will, evidently. It was my nature to feel pleasure in yielding to an authority

14:31.560 --> 14:37.720
supported like hers, and to bend, where my conscience and self-respect permitted,

14:38.340 --> 14:40.240
to an active will.

14:40.240 --> 14:45.200
And what business have you here? she continued. It is not your place.

14:45.720 --> 14:50.620
Mary and I sit in the kitchen sometimes, because at home we like to be free, even to license,

14:51.060 --> 14:53.980
but you are a visitor and must go into the parlour.

14:54.800 --> 14:56.480
I am very well here.

14:57.020 --> 15:00.400
Not at all, with Hannah bustling about and covering you with flour.

15:01.520 --> 15:04.680
Besides, the fire is too hot for you, interposed Mary.

15:04.680 --> 15:10.800
To be sure, added her sister, come, you must be obedient. And still holding my hand,

15:10.860 --> 15:13.760
she made me rise and led me into the inner room.

15:14.440 --> 15:19.140
Sit there, she said, placing me on the sofa, while we take our things off and get the tea ready.

15:19.640 --> 15:25.020
It is another privilege we exercise in our little moorland home, to prepare our own meals when we

15:25.020 --> 15:30.900
are so inclined, or when Hannah is baking, brewing, washing, or ironing. She closed the

15:30.900 --> 15:37.140
door, leaving me soulless with Mr. St. John, who sat opposite, a book or newspaper in his hand.

15:37.580 --> 15:41.020
I examined first the parlour, and then its occupant.

15:41.600 --> 15:47.520
The parlour was rather a small room, very plainly furnished, yet comfortable, because clean and

15:47.520 --> 15:53.400
neat. The old-fashioned chairs were very bright, and the walnut wood table was like a looking glass.

15:53.960 --> 15:59.600
A few strange antique portraits of the men and women of other days decorated the stained walls.

15:59.600 --> 16:04.540
A cupboard with glass doors contained some books and an ancient set of china.

16:05.220 --> 16:10.940
There was no superfluous ornament in the room, not one modern piece of furniture save a brace

16:10.940 --> 16:17.340
of work-boxes and a lady's desk in rosewood which stood on a side table. Everything,

16:17.500 --> 16:22.420
including the carpet and curtains, looked at once well worn and well saved.

16:23.620 --> 16:27.640
Mr. St. John, sitting as still as one of the dusty pictures on the walls,

16:27.640 --> 16:34.040
keeping his eyes fixed on the page he perused, and his lips mutely sealed, was easy enough to

16:34.040 --> 16:40.860
examine. Had he been a statue instead of a man, he could not have been easier. He was young,

16:41.020 --> 16:48.320
perhaps from twenty-eight to thirty, tall, slender. His face riveted the eye. It was like a

16:48.320 --> 16:56.440
Greek face, very pure in outline, quite a straight, classic nose, quite an Athenian mouth and chin.

16:56.960 --> 17:03.160
It is seldom, indeed, an English face come so near the antique models as did his. He might

17:03.160 --> 17:08.860
well be a little shocked at the irregularity of my liniments, his own being so harmonious.

17:09.400 --> 17:15.660
His eyes were large and blue, with brown lashes. His high forehead, colorless as ivory,

17:16.040 --> 17:19.580
was partially streaked over by careless locks of fair hair.

17:20.760 --> 17:27.380
This is a gentle delineation, is it not, reader? Yet he whom it describes scarcely impressed one

17:27.380 --> 17:33.000
with the idea of a gentle, a yielding, an impressible, or even of a placid nature.

17:33.860 --> 17:38.960
Quiescent as he now sat, there was something about his nostril, his mouth, his brow,

17:39.380 --> 17:45.180
which to my perceptions indicated elements within either restless, or hard, or eager.

17:45.880 --> 17:52.400
He did not speak to me one word, nor even direct to me one glance, till his sisters returned.

17:53.440 --> 17:58.580
Diana, as she passed in and out, in the course of preparing tea, brought me a little cake,

17:58.760 --> 18:00.140
baked on the top of the oven.

18:00.880 --> 18:05.880
Eat that now, she said, you must be hungry. Hannah says you have had nothing but some

18:05.880 --> 18:11.780
gruel since breakfast. I did not refuse it, for my appetite was awakened and keen.

18:11.780 --> 18:17.360
Mr. Rivers now closed his book, approached the table, and as he took a seat fixed his

18:17.360 --> 18:22.960
blue pictorial-looking eyes full on me. There was an unceremonious directness,

18:23.420 --> 18:28.860
a searching, decided steadfastness in his gaze now, which told that intention,

18:29.320 --> 18:32.980
and not diffidence, had hitherto kept it averted from the stranger.

18:33.740 --> 18:35.600
You are very hungry, he said.

18:35.600 --> 18:43.800
I am, sir. It is my way, it always was my way, by instinct, ever to meet the brief with brevity,

18:44.300 --> 18:50.500
the direct with plainness. It is well for you that a low fever has forced you to abstain for

18:50.500 --> 18:54.720
the last three days. There would have been danger in yielding to the cravings of your

18:54.720 --> 18:59.280
appetite at first. Now you may eat, though still not immoderately.

18:59.980 --> 19:07.140
I trust I shall not eat long at your expense, sir, was my very clumsily contrived, unpolished

19:07.140 --> 19:13.000
answer. No, he said coolly, when you have indicated to us the residence of your friends,

19:13.080 --> 19:19.660
we can write to them, and you may be restored to home. That, I must plainly tell you, is out of my

19:19.660 --> 19:26.800
power to do, being absolutely without home and friends. The three looked at me, but not

19:26.800 --> 19:32.000
trustfully. I felt there was no suspicion in their glances, there was more of curiosity.

19:32.860 --> 19:38.180
I speak particularly of the young ladies. St. John's eyes, though clear enough in a literal

19:38.180 --> 19:44.640
sense, in a figurative one were difficult to fathom. He seemed to use them rather as instruments to

19:44.640 --> 19:51.440
search other people's thoughts, than as agents to reveal his own. The which combination of keenness

19:51.440 --> 19:56.640
and reserve was considerably more calculated to embarrass than to encourage.

19:58.500 --> 20:03.300
Do you mean to say, he asked, that you are completely isolated from every connection?

20:04.260 --> 20:10.640
I do. Not a tie links me to any living thing. Not a claim do I possess to admittance under

20:10.640 --> 20:18.120
any roof in England. A most singular position at your age. Here I saw his glance directed to my

20:18.120 --> 20:24.160
hands, which were folded on the table before me. I wondered what he sought there. His words

20:24.160 --> 20:31.280
soon explained the quest. You have never been married? You are a spinster? Diana laughed.

20:31.340 --> 20:38.180
Why, she can't be above seventeen or eighteen years old, St. John, said she. I am near nineteen,

20:38.540 --> 20:46.120
but I am not married. No. I felt a burning glow mount to my face, for bitter and agitating

20:46.120 --> 20:52.500
recollections were awakened by the allusion to marriage. They all saw the embarrassment

20:52.500 --> 20:58.900
and the emotion. Diana and Mary relieved me by turning their eyes elsewhere than to my crimsoned

20:58.900 --> 21:04.720
visage. But the colder and sterner brother continued to gaze till the trouble he had

21:04.720 --> 21:10.680
excited forced out tears as well as colour. Where did you last reside, he now asked?

21:10.680 --> 21:16.720
You are too inquisitive, St. John, murmured Mary in a low voice, but he leaned over the

21:16.720 --> 21:23.600
table and required an answer by a second firm and piercing look. The name of the place where

21:23.600 --> 21:32.860
and of the person with whom I lived is my secret, I replied concisely. Which, if you like, you have,

21:32.860 --> 21:37.980
in my opinion, a right to keep, both from St. John and every other questioner, remarked Diana.

21:39.060 --> 21:44.360
Yet if I know nothing about you or your history, I cannot help you, he said. And you need help,

21:44.560 --> 21:51.480
do you not? I need it, and I seek it so far, sir, that some true philanthropist will put me in the

21:51.480 --> 21:57.820
way of getting work which I can do, and the remuneration for which will keep me, but if in

21:57.820 --> 22:04.920
the barest necessities of life. I know not whether I am a true philanthropist, yet I am willing to

22:05.440 --> 22:11.640
utmost of my power in a purpose so honest. First, then, tell me what you have been accustomed to do

22:11.640 --> 22:19.000
and what you can do. I had now swallowed my tea. I was mightily refreshed by the beverage, as much

22:19.000 --> 22:27.340
so as a giant with wine, it gave me new tone to my unstrung nerves, and it enabled me to address this

22:27.340 --> 22:34.500
penetrating young judge steadily. Mr. Rivers, I said, turning to him, and looking at him as he

22:34.500 --> 22:40.880
looked at me, openly and without diffidence, you and your sisters have done me a great service,

22:41.320 --> 22:47.020
the greatest man can do to his fellow being. You have rescued me by your noble hospitality from

22:47.020 --> 22:54.940
death. This benefit conferred gives you an unlimited claim on my gratitude, and a claim to a certain

22:54.940 --> 23:01.200
extent on my confidence. I will tell you as much of the history of the wanderer you have harbored,

23:01.200 --> 23:06.680
as I can tell, without compromising my own peace of mind, my own security,

23:06.900 --> 23:14.360
moral and physical, and that of others. I am an orphan, the daughter of a clergyman.

23:14.980 --> 23:20.940
My parents died before I could know them. I was brought up a dependent, educated in a charitable

23:20.940 --> 23:27.040
institution. I will even tell you the name of the establishment, where I passed six years as a pupil

23:27.040 --> 23:33.340
and two as a teacher, Lowood Orphan Asylum. You will have heard of it, Mr. Rivers.

23:33.860 --> 23:39.580
The Reverend Robert Brocklehurst is the treasurer. I have heard of Mr. Brocklehurst,

23:40.060 --> 23:47.120
and I have seen the school. I left Lowood nearly a year since to become a private governess.

23:47.360 --> 23:53.500
I obtained a good situation and was happy. This place I was obliged to leave four days before I

23:53.500 --> 23:59.960
came here. The reason of my departure I cannot and ought not to explain. It would be useless,

24:00.440 --> 24:07.040
dangerous, and would sound incredible. No blame attached to me. I am as free from culpability

24:07.040 --> 24:14.160
as any one of you three. Miserable I am and must be for a time, for the catastrophe which drove me

24:14.160 --> 24:22.080
from a house I had found a paradise was of a strange and direful nature. I observed but two

24:22.080 --> 24:29.300
points in planning my departure—speed, secrecy. To secure these I had to leave behind me everything

24:29.300 --> 24:35.000
I possessed except a small parcel, which in my hurry and trouble of mind I forgot to take out of

24:35.000 --> 24:41.920
the coach that brought me to Whitcross. To this neighbourhood then I came quite destitute. I slept

24:41.920 --> 24:48.160
two nights in the open air and wandered about two days without crossing a threshold. But twice in

24:48.160 --> 24:54.700
space of time did I taste food, and it was when brought by hunger, exhaustion, and despair almost

24:54.700 --> 25:01.320
to the last gasp that you, Mr. Rivers, forbade me to perish of want at your door and took me under

25:01.320 --> 25:09.080
the shelter of your roof. I know all your sisters have done for me, for I have not been insensible

25:09.080 --> 25:17.140
during my seeming torpor, and I owe to their spontaneous, genuine, genial compassion as large

25:17.140 --> 25:20.180
as your evangelical charity."

25:21.120 --> 25:25.420
"'Don't make her talk any more now, St. John,' said Diana, as I paused.

25:25.480 --> 25:30.460
"'She is evidently not yet fit for excitement. Come to the sofa and sit down, Miss Elliot.'

25:31.260 --> 25:38.300
I gave an involuntary half-start at hearing the alias. I had forgotten my new name. Mr. Rivers,

25:38.420 --> 25:41.180
whom nothing seemed to escape, noticed it at once.

25:41.700 --> 25:44.580
"'You said your name was Jane Elliot,' he observed.

25:45.240 --> 25:50.800
I did say so, and it is the name by which I think it expedient to be called at present,

25:51.320 --> 25:55.840
but it is not my real name, and when I hear it, it sounds strange to me.

25:56.720 --> 25:58.550
"'Your real name you will not give?'

25:59.360 --> 26:04.500
No, I fear discovery above all things, and whatever disclosure would lead to it I avoid.'

26:05.480 --> 26:08.120
"'You are quite right, I am sure,' said Diana.

26:08.460 --> 26:11.120
"'Now do, brother, let her be at peace a while.'

26:11.680 --> 26:16.360
But when St. John had mused a few moments, he recommended as imperturbably,

26:16.360 --> 26:18.560
and with as much acumen as ever,

26:18.780 --> 26:22.320
"'You would not like to be long dependent on our hospitality.

26:22.520 --> 26:27.240
You would wish, I see, to dispense as soon as may be with my sister's compassion,

26:27.680 --> 26:32.560
and above all with my charity. I am quite sensible of the distinction drawn,

26:32.680 --> 26:37.600
nor do I resent it. It is just. You desire to be independent of us.'

26:38.400 --> 26:46.160
I do. I have already said so. Show me how to work, or how to seek work. That is all I now ask.

26:46.320 --> 26:51.760
Then let me go, if it be but to the meanest cottage. But till then, allow me to stay here.'

26:52.640 --> 26:56.220
I dread another essay of the horrors of homeless destitution.

26:57.640 --> 27:01.820
"'Indeed you shall stay here,' said Diana, putting her white hand on my head.

27:01.820 --> 27:08.080
"'You shall,' repeated Mary, in the tone of undemonstrative sincerity which seemed natural to

27:08.080 --> 27:12.420
her. "'My sisters, you see, have a pleasure in keeping you,' said Mr. St. John,

27:12.520 --> 27:16.740
as they would have a pleasure in keeping and cherishing a half-frozen bird some wintry wind

27:16.740 --> 27:21.640
might have driven through their casement. I feel more inclined to put you in the way of keeping

27:21.640 --> 27:31.800
yourself, and shall endeavour to do so. But observe, my sphere is narrow. I am but the

27:31.800 --> 27:38.340
homeless sort, and if you are inclined to despise the day of small things, seek some more efficient

27:38.340 --> 27:44.200
sucker than such as I can offer.' "'She has already said that she is willing to do anything honest

27:44.200 --> 27:49.500
she can do,' answered Diana for me. "'And you know, St. John, she has no choice of helpers.

27:49.860 --> 27:52.710
She is forced to put up with such crusty people as you.'

27:54.300 --> 27:59.140
"'I will be a dressmaker. I will be a plain workwoman. I will be a servant,

27:59.140 --> 28:02.100
a nurse-girl, if I can be no better,' I answered.

28:03.200 --> 28:06.040
"'Right,' said Mr. St. John quite coolly.

28:06.200 --> 28:10.600
"'If such is your spirit, I promise to aid you in my own time and way.'

28:11.360 --> 28:15.420
He now resumed the book with which he had been occupied before tea.

28:15.960 --> 28:22.340
I soon withdrew, for I had talked as much and sat up as long as my present strength would permit.

